{"TopicId":197935,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal Space Program 2 to be released in 2022 [Discussion Thread]","CreatedByName":"Arco123","CreatedById":201477,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T17:18:00Z","PageNum":20,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mcwaffles2003","CreatedById":180102,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-26T11:56:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036169\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632593773\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Generic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, A Generic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just want to say one thing:\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe delays are kinda\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Esus\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter the reception the game got after announcement they probably were allowed to vastly expand the scope of the game at the cost of delaying it\u0027s release. Along the way of negotiating the future of the project it seems like there were some disagreement among the leaders of star theory with the people at T2 hence the debacle and creation of intercept games. So the studio switch was a cause for a lot of delay, then there\u0027s onboarding a bunch of new people to a WIP project, then there was covid... So to think delays would be unexpected is a tad ridiculous...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bet the original KSP 2 from the announcement didn\u0027t have nearly as many features and, at worst, might have even been a rushed hack job with little regard for the original title.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust my guesses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jeb10","CreatedById":216344,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-27T10:10:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that KSP 2 won\u0027t delay again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E. I\u0027ve been waiting for this since 2018! Although my laptop\u0027s graphic card\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0probably not compatable with it but I just need to low down the graphic setting and it ready to go! I wonder what the main menu would look like cuz KSP 1 main menu is pretty boring and not many option lol \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LezRowl","CreatedById":213344,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-27T11:35:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake your time developers.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PlutoISaPlanet","CreatedById":206057,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-28T01:02:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just can\u0027t wait for that sweet music! Maybe we get some early track releases...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nirgal","CreatedById":211448,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-29T17:57:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632742550\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LezRowl\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/27/2021 at 12:35 PM, LezRowl said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake your time developers.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022the-office-no.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.00\u0022 height=\u0022140\u0022 width=\u0022250\u0022 src=\u0022https://c.tenor.com/yZXjvQffRWEAAAAC/the-office-no.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas Gaming","CreatedById":196160,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-29T19:14:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs someone who \u0022plays\u0022 Star Citizen (8 years in alpha and 10 years till release estimate) I am all for you guys taking ALL THE TIME YOU NEED to put out a killer, bug free game! I\u0027ve gotten more than my moneys worth from Kerbal 1 (thanks moding community) and I\u0027m sure Kerbal 2 could be the same... but do not do what Elite Dangerous did with their last DLC and put out a product full of bugs and lacking optimization! My $.02\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-29T20:21:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224037613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632938255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211448\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nirgal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nirgal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://c.tenor.com/yZXjvQffRWEAAAAC/the-office-no.gif\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022the-office-no.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.00\u0022 height=\u0022140\u0022 width=\u0022250\u0022 src=\u0022https://c.tenor.com/yZXjvQffRWEAAAAC/the-office-no.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027know, we\u0027d be fine paying full price (60 dollars) for a beta that gets updated just like regular KSP....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr.Evil","CreatedById":209322,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-29T21:01:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224037686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632946866\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027know, we\u0027d be fine paying full price (60 dollars) for a beta that gets updated just like regular KSP....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a alpha/beta would be released soon, with for example only the Kerbin System... I would buy immediately. XD\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-30T10:46:26Z\u0022 title=\u002209/30/2021 10:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 30, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Mr.Evil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Egrammar correction\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alphaprior","CreatedById":185480,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-30T07:20:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632737435\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeb10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/27/2021 at 1:10 PM, jeb10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that KSP 2 won\u0027t delay again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E. I\u0027ve been waiting for this since 2018! Although my laptop\u0027s graphic card\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0probably not compatable with it but I just need to low down the graphic setting and it ready to go! I wonder what the main menu would look like cuz KSP 1 main menu is pretty boring and not many option lol \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps you should invest on a new system then. Not a laptop but a full PC desktop to enjoy KSP2 properly and whatever else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Generic Kerbal","CreatedById":211685,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-03T09:44:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224037650\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632942857\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196160\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas Gaming\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/29/2021 at 10:14 PM, Atlas Gaming said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs someone who \u0022plays\u0022 Star Citizen (8 years in alpha and 10 years till release estimate) I am all for you guys taking ALL THE TIME YOU NEED to put out a killer, bug free game! I\u0027ve gotten more than my moneys worth from Kerbal 1 (thanks moding community) and I\u0027m sure Kerbal 2 could be the same... but do not do what Elite Dangerous did with their last DLC and put out a product full of bugs and lacking optimization! My $.02\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but Star Citizen is already available for everyone to play, while the KSP 2 is not\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would\u0027ve agreed with you if there was an open alpha/beta test for KSP 2, but sadly there isn\u0027t\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224037686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632946866\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/29/2021 at 11:21 PM, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY\u0027know, we\u0027d be fine paying full price (60 dollars) for a beta that gets updated just like regular KSP....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would\u0027ve been the happiest man in the world if we had a playable demo or something\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven with no tutorial, outer solar systems and not all p\u003Cspan\u003Earts included\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-10-03T10:07:53Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2021 10:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by A Generic Kerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EGrammatical mistake lol\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jack White","CreatedById":216567,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-04T12:14:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any ways to join beta? Im exited that\u0027s the second game will be released next year.\u00A0 Would try out early builds if there is a way to.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"asap1","CreatedById":209758,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-04T13:47:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell take your time as much as the kraken is entertaining to watch it\u0027s not always so nice\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheOrbitalMechanic","CreatedById":216179,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-14T18:04:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632737435\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeb10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/27/2021 at 4:10 AM, jeb10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that KSP 2 won\u0027t delay again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E. I\u0027ve been waiting for this since 2018! Although my laptop\u0027s graphic card\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0probably not compatable with it but I just need to low down the graphic setting and it ready to go! I wonder what the main menu would look like cuz KSP 1 main menu is pretty boring and not many option lol \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe good news is, there hasn\u0027t been a single (announced) delay in over 10 months! To contrast, there were delays every 3-6 months through 2019 and 2020, so it seems like they have a release timeframe that works and a good handle on what they\u0027re doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Generic Kerbal","CreatedById":211685,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-14T21:32:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224043008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634234649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216179\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheOrbitalMechanic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, TheOrbitalMechanic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe good news is, there hasn\u0027t been a single (announced) delay in over 10 months! To contrast, there were delays every 3-6 months through 2019 and 2020, so it seems like they have a release timeframe that works and a good handle on what they\u0027re doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill no exact release date \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Staticalliam7","CreatedById":216180,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-14T23:23:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224043008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634234649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216179\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheOrbitalMechanic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, TheOrbitalMechanic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036699\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632737435\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jeb10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/27/2021 at 6:10 AM, jeb10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that KSP 2 won\u0027t delay again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E. I\u0027ve been waiting for this since 2018! Although my laptop\u0027s graphic card\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0probably not compatable with it but I just need to low down the graphic setting and it ready to go! I wonder what the main menu would look like cuz KSP 1 main menu is pretty boring and not many option lol \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe good news is, there hasn\u0027t been a single (announced) delay in over 10 months! To contrast, there were delays every 3-6 months through 2019 and 2020, so it seems like they have a release timeframe that works and a good handle on what they\u0027re doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t say that! You are going to jinx us all!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224031430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221631564556\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262881\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gilflo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/13/2021 at 4:22 PM, gilflo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like KSP 2 will not be available on Mac OSX, that\u2019s what i see on Private division. \u00A0If it\u2019s true it\u2019s a shame for all Mac players. I just hope i am wrong!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple solution:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep one: Get a sledge hammer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep 2: Smash said mac\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep 3: Build a pc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep 4: Download Steam\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep 5: Download KSP 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStep 6: Profit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tw1","CreatedById":59717,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-15T05:53:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would rather it be good, than it be here sooner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Generic Kerbal","CreatedById":211685,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-17T09:50:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224043154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634277184\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259717\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tw1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/15/2021 at 8:53 AM, Tw1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would rather it be good, than it be here sooner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like a beta test even if it\u0027s buggy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-17T18:05:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if they will tell us when they enter Alpha, Beta, etc?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-17T18:18:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224043062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634247128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Generic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/14/2021 at 10:32 PM, A Generic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill no exact release date \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould you want an \u0027exact\u0027 date that may well end up moving?\u00A0 Or sticking to with major bugs that they had to leave to make the deadline?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas Gaming","CreatedById":196160,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T00:14:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d preffer 2023 to be sure they work bugs out and they can offer beta to developers in 2022 so that at release we can have MechJeb and other mods that everyone uses.\u00A0 A modded UI to resemble the Kerbal 1 would be awesome too\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TLTay","CreatedById":184633,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T00:36:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044566\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634602454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196160\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas Gaming\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Atlas Gaming said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d preffer 2023 to be sure they work bugs out and they can offer beta to developers in 2022 so that at release we can have MechJeb and other mods that everyone uses.\u00A0 A modded UI to resemble the Kerbal 1 would be awesome too\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother year delay? Please no. I was initially told in 2019 that I\u0027d be playing KSP2 in early 2020. It\u0027s almost 2022. I\u0027m fairly patient and don\u0027t want to seem ungrateful to the devs, but I\u0027d really like something positive to help take my mind off of an increasingly disastrous and dystopian world.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Generic Kerbal","CreatedById":211685,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T08:41:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044566\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634602454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196160\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas Gaming\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Atlas Gaming said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d preffer 2023 to be sure they work bugs out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHell no, no more delays. I was promised to play in early 2020, and now it\u0027s almost 2022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044571\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634603811\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184633\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TLTay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, TLTay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noffer beta to developers in 2022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffer beta to everyone who wants it. I\u0027ve waited enough already\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634494723\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/17/2021 at 9:18 PM, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr sticking to with major bugs that they had to leave\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would prefer playing with bugs rather than not playing at all\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 1 had alpha and beta versions, so I see no problem doing that with KSP 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T18:05:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044673\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634632913\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Generic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, A Generic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044047\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634494723\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/17/2021 at 7:18 PM, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr sticking to with major bugs that they had to leave\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would prefer playing with bugs rather than not playing at all\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 1 had alpha and beta versions, so I see no problem doing that with KSP 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if those bugs made it unplayable for you?\u00A0 As many claimed some of the KSP1 bugs frequently did.\u00A0 Personally I found some very annoying, but not really \u0027unplayable\u0027, although some were quite close, but then again I\u0027m a pretty easy going type.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, unlike KSP2, KSP1 needed the alpha/beta early access model to get attention and prove it\u0027s viability, and bugs were expected as a result.\u00A0 The sequel needs to hit the ground running with a decent quality product or flop through bad reviews.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A Generic Kerbal","CreatedById":211685,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T21:15:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634666748\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if those bugs made it unplayable for you?\u00A0 As many claimed some of the KSP1 bugs frequently did.\u00A0 Personally I found some very annoying, but not really \u0027unplayable\u0027, although some were quite close, but then again I\u0027m a pretty easy going type.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, unlike KSP2, KSP1 needed the alpha/beta early access model to get attention and prove it\u0027s viability, and bugs were expected as a result.\u00A0 The sequel needs to hit the ground running with a decent quality product or flop through bad reviews.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a bug makes the game unplayable, the game is DEFINITELY not in the alpha/beta stage\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Or it was made by Bethesda)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-10-19T21:33:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224044891\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221634678116\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022A Generic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, A Generic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a bug makes the game unplayable, the game is DEFINITELY not in the alpha/beta stage\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Or it was made by Bethesda)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo argument there, but a prominent, if not critical,\u00A0 bug in a beta release could have serious PR consequences.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot everyone would be as accepting as you or I.\u00A0 Or as understanding that a \u0027beta\u0027 is not finished product so problems are to be expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}